# LotuS2 Parameters 

> recommended by Galaxy Training: https://training.galaxyproject.org/training-material/topics/microbiome/tutorials/lotus2-identifying-fungi/tutorial.html

"Clustering algorithm": VSEARCH

"Taxonomy aligner for taxonomic profiling of OTUs": Lamda, LCA against custom reference database
    "Using reference database": ITS fungi specific (UNITE)

In "Other Clustering Options":
     "Minimum size of dereplicated raw reads (optional)": 10:1, 5:2, 3:3

In "Other Taxonomy Options": 
      "Amplicon type": ITS2
      "Tax group": fungal 18S/23S/ITS annotation

# Outputs
OTU.biom
OTU.phylo.nwk
